<section class="brand--attorney-generals-office brand__border-color organisation__brand-border-top organisation__section-wrap organisation__margin-bottom" id="what-we-do">
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--padding gem-c-heading--margin-bottom-2  ">What Bona Vacantia does</h2>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
    
          <p></p>
<div class="govspeak">
<p>‘Bona Vacantia’ means vacant goods and is the name given to ownerless property, which by law passes to the Crown.</p>

<p>The Treasury Solicitor acts for the Crown to administer the estates of people who die intestate (without a Will) and without known kin (entitled blood relatives) and collect the assets of dissolved companies and other various ownerless goods in England and Wales.</p>

<p><abbr title="Bona Vacantia">BVD</abbr> is part of the <a class="brand__color" href="/government/organisations/government-legal-department">Government Legal Department</a>.</p>
</div>

          <p>
            <a href="/government/organisations/bona-vacantia/about" class="brand__color">
              Read more about what we do
            </a>
          </p>

</div>
    </div>

      <div class="column-one-third">
        <h3 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--font-size-19 gem-c-heading--margin-bottom-2  ">Follow us</h3>

          <div class="gem-c-share-links brand--attorney-generals-office gem-c-share-links--stacked" data-module="track-click">

